Install Node.js: Make sure you have Node.js installed. You can download it from nodejs.org.

#Create a New Project Directory:
mkdir cesiumjs-bhel-project
cd cesiumjs-bhel-project

#Initialize the Project:
npm init -y

#Install Cesium:
npm install cesium

#Set Up the Project Structure:
#Create an index.html file:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CesiumJS BEL Project</title>
    <style>
        #cesiumContainer {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100vh;
            display: block;
        }
        #layer-toggle-buttons {
            position: absolute;
            top: 10px;
            left: 10px;
            z-index: 1;
        }
    </style>
    <link href="https://cesium.com/downloads/cesiumjs/releases/1.80/Build/Cesium/Widgets/widgets.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <div id="cesiumContainer"></div>
    <div id="layer-toggle-buttons"></div>
    <script src="https://cesium.com/downloads/cesiumjs/releases/1.80/Build/Cesium/Cesium.js"></script>
    <script src="app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
#Create an app.js file and paste the provided code into it.

#Run a Local Server: To serve the files locally, you can use a simple server like http-server.
npx http-server

#Open the Project in Your Browser: Open the URL provided by the local server (e.g., http://localhost:8080) to see your CesiumJS project in action.
